reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Soft light weight fabric with stretch. No gap at the waist. Amazon recommends to size up so I did. Normally a 4 to got a 6 and it is perfect waist, thighs and length. Will be getting in other colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect wide-legged jeans for petites
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I’m so happy skinny jeans are out and wide-legged jeans are back in again! These jeans look great because they are fitted though the waist and hips, and the wide leg doesn’t overpower my petite frame. And they are the perfect length! The material is super stretchy, yet they don’t get stretched out. How did they do that? I don’t know, but I love it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice jeans with good stretch
reviews.reviewText: I am 5’5” 145 lbs and size 8 fit me very well. They are a tiny bit snug around the waist, but that’s because I need to lose a few pounds. They are otherwise comfy, they have a nice stretch without looking like those yoga pants that look like jeans, I hate those! I want my yoga pants to look like yoga pants and my jeans to look like jeans. The color is nice and quality seems great, I’m glad I bought these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Smell horrible and can’t wash smell out.
reviews.reviewText: Cute pants. Nice width. Little short however I have long legs. Reeks of patchouly. I’ve washed them 3 times and the smell is still so pungent I can’t wear them. I had to take a shower to get the smell off my legs after trying them on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit like a Glove for Women with Curves
reviews.reviewText: Hi, I was pleasantly surprised to try on these jeans when they arrived. They fit perfectly! I am 5'5, 135 pounds with curves. My waist is quite a bit smaller than my hips, so I often have difficulty finding jeans that the waist isn't much too big, looking strange. Glad to report, these jeans fit well, with a bit of stretch. I bought a size 10, which is larger than i normally buy, I usually buy an 8. However, the reviews were spot on.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Lol what is this
reviews.reviewText: I got the pink- I'm seriously annoyed with everyone who had left a positive review. These are by far the worst pants I've ever bought. I don't understand why they look like this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Definitely NOT a clean or bright white.Not even white.It’s a yellowy, off-white, that looks like you’ve washed it in hard water, with very dirty and grimy sheets and clothing, a zillion times.I’ve bought what I thought were bright white jeans, from several different sellers on Amazon, only to be sent the identical pair of unbranded pants; same color, same design, same material.What a hassle and waste of time and resources, just to have to send all of them back!SELLERS: Please, I implore you, correctly advertise your product color in the description. It’s not any more work to type “off-white” vs incorrectly advertising the color as “white”, when you add the color description and/or choices. It’s just 3 more keystrokes. Four if you include a hyphen. Geez.2 out of 5 stars:1) the fit is true to size: +1 star2) the material is nice and soft: + 1 star3) not white, as advertised: 0 stars4) had to return: 0 stars5) waste of time, effort, resources: 0 stars

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Length my be a tad too long if you're 5'2"
reviews.reviewText: Love the fit. I'm 5'2" and the jeans were a little too long for me however, I did get them hemmed and they perfect now.
